{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:30:45.086304+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have all the information needed. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## How to Run & Build This React Admin App\n\nThis is a **Vite + React + TypeScript** admin dashboard (built on the `vite-react-ts-admin` template). It uses **Yarn** as its package manager.\n\n### Initial Setup\n\nThe project provides a [Taskfile](https://taskfile.dev/) with an `init` command that automates first-time setup:\n\n```bash\n# Install Task (if you don't have it), then:\ntask init\n```\n\nThis runs `cp envs/.env.local .env` (creating the root `.env`) and `yarn install`. If you don't use Task, do the same manually:\n\n```bash\ncp envs/.env.local .env\nyarn install\n```\n\n### Running Locally\n\n```bash\nyarn dev          # Starts Vite dev server on http://local.lantron.ltd:10086 (--host)\nyarn dev:stg      # Starts dev server with staging environment config\n```\n\nThe dev server is configured with CORS enabled and HMR over WebSocket. The `--host` flag on `dev` exposes it on the network.\n\n### Environment Files\n\nThere are three pre-configured environments under `envs/`:\n\n| File | `NODE_ENV` | API Base URL |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.env.local` | `local` | `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd` |\n| `.env.stg` | `stg` | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` |\n| `.env.prod` | `prod` | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n\nAll set `VITE_PORT=10086` and `VITE_BASE_URL=./`. The Vite config (`vite.config.ts`) loads from a root `.env` if present, otherwise falls back to `envs/.env.${NODE_ENV}`.\n\n### Building for Different Environments\n\n```bash\nyarn build         # Builds with mode=prod (uses NODE_ENV=local by default)\nyarn build:stg     # Builds with NODE_ENV=stg, mode=test  (staging)\nyarn build:prod    # Builds with NODE_ENV=prod, mode=production\n```\n\nAll builds output to the `dist/` directory.\n\n### Previewing a Build\n\n```bash\nyarn serve         # Runs `vite preview --host` to serve the dist/ folder locally\n```\n\n### Docker\n\nThe `Dockerfile` uses a two-stage build:\n1. **Builder stage** (`node:lts-alpine`): runs `yarn` and `yarn build` (defaults to local env).\n2. **Runtime stage** (`nginx:alpine`): copies `dist/` into nginx and serves on **port 80** using the included `nginx.conf`.\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t admin-app .\ndocker run -p 8080:80 admin-app\n```\n\n### Linting\n\n```bash\nyarn lint          # Run ESLint\nyarn fix           # Run ESLint with --fix\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 933, "prompt_tokens": 8072, "total_tokens": 9005, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 263, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6784, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0004605552, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001993152, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00026124}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871432-RmX8HjkxomDISdRAZM38", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea435-89f5-7933-a83f-88d6e5f58347-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8072, "output_tokens": 933, "total_tokens": 9005, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 6784}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 263}}}}]}}}
